rlm-git-changed

Pick a file changed since the fork point of the current branch from
the default remote branch (origin/HEAD) using fzf, then open it in
$EDITOR. The diff preview for the selected file is shown in the fzf
preview pane. Press Ctrl-P to cycle the preview pane height.

Entries are sorted by recently-selected first, then by file mtime
descending for entries that have never been picked. Within
previously-picked entries, the most-recent pick wins.

MRU history is recorded by the shared helper
_rlm-git-changed-history in ~/.cache/rlm-git-changed/history.tsv,
scoped per repo via repo_key (md5 of the absolute git_root). The
legacy per-repo files at ~/.cache/git-changed/<md5>.history are
folded in on first use and then left in place.

ENVIRONMENT
  EDITOR   Editor to open the selected file (falls back to vi).

REQUIRES
  git, fzf, python3, md5 or md5sum
